title: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup() does not return the expected output
description: Bug 49235: When invoking the onStartup() method of ServletContainerInitializer using a Set<Class<?> classSet, the output is 'MySomeClass', but I was expecting the output to be 'MySomeClass'. This is not yet implemented in the Servlet 3.0 spec. My code worked fine on Glassfish 3.0.
EB: The classSet does not return the expected class.
SR: Update the implementation of the ServletContainerInitializer to return the expected output and ensure compatibility with the Servlet 3.0 spec.
